INSTALL THE REQUIRED SOFTWARE
1.) Python 2.5 or 2.6 (http://www.python.org)
2.) Python Mutagen (for mp3 header parsing) (http://code.google.com/p/mutagen/)
3.) Lame MP3 Encoder (http://lame.sourceforge.net/)

RUN THE SOFTWARE

1.) Change the examples/default.cfg file to your liking.
2.) Create a new examples/file.list file with the MP3 files you want to play
    (I like to just do 'find /abs/path/to/dir -name *.mp3 > examples/file.list').
3.) Install 'sudo python setup.py install'.
4.) Ensure that the bin/ocradio script is in your path.
4.) Run ocradio with the config file 'ocradio -c examples/default.cfg'